author: rse
msg: After the third interaction now we have it:
Dynamic Shared Object (DSO) support for IBM's AIX.
This is accomplished by using DSO emulation code because AIX <= 4.2 don't have
dlopen() and AIX 4.2 has a broken one.  But with the emulation code it works

author: rse
msg: Fix nasty compiler warnings under AIX 4.2 because there we need
NET_SIZE_T=size_t according to the include files and not NET_SIZE_T=int as the
manual pages of getsockname() etc. indicate.
